        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41265",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=synchro",
                        "name": "synchro",
                        "displayName": "Marcus Bointon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, this is still present in 1.10.6 and it means I can't use ZF at all!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=synchro",
                        "name": "synchro",
                        "displayName": "Marcus Bointon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-30T09:29:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-30T09:29:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41268",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=synchro",
                        "name": "synchro",
                        "displayName": "Marcus Bointon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A quick grep finds me 97 instances of class_exists without a 'false' second parameter (though I'm not trying to resurrect #10053 here). I don't know if it's worth me generating what would be a pretty huge patch for all of them, plus I don't know ZF well enough to be able to fix all of them sensibly - are partial patches welcome?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=synchro",
                        "name": "synchro",
                        "displayName": "Marcus Bointon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-30T10:10:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-30T10:10:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41364",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=vipsoft",
                        "name": "vipsoft",
                        "displayName": "Anthon Pang, VIP Software Technologies Inc.",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "(I've deleted my earlier comment as it was off-topic.)\r\n\r\nZF-6660 and ZF-6591 were special cases.  In general, we want class_exists() without the second parameter (false) whenever it precedes a loadClass(), because it allows other autoloaders to execute.\r\n\r\nIf you've implemented your own autoloader, just make sure it doesn't throw an exception when the file\/class is not found.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=vipsoft",
                        "name": "vipsoft",
                        "displayName": "Anthon Pang, VIP Software Technologies Inc.",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-06T22:50:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-06T22:50:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41368",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=synchro",
                        "name": "synchro",
                        "displayName": "Marcus Bointon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It's a shame you deleted your comment as it contained two of the instances that I'd run into! I'm calling Zend_Feed:import, which correctly uses Zend_Loader to load Zend_Http_Client, which correctly uses Zend_Loader to load Zend_Uri, but unfortunately that doesn't use Zend_Loader and calls class_exists before trying to load Zend_Uri_Http and thus breaks. Consistency is the key here, and your previously posted fix works perfectly in this case.  \"allowing other autoloaders to execute\" is precisely what's breaking ZF; my autoloader is not compatible with ZF, nor should it need to be, and it's why Zend_Loader exists. Zend_Loader DOES call class_exists without the second param, so we should be using it everywhere, and not clumsily circumventing it randomly. As it stands it renders ZF unusable as a component library; if I can't load a component and call a function in it without breaking my app, it's broken.\r\nI'll post a patch for just this specific case rather than trying to fix anything bigger.\r\nGiven that ZF2 has a very clear aim of doing *everything* with Zend_Loader via autoload, it seems silly not to head in vaguely the same direction in 1.x.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=synchro",
                        "name": "synchro",
                        "displayName": "Marcus Bointon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-07T00:20:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-07T00:20:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41380",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=synchro",
                        "name": "synchro",
                        "displayName": "Marcus Bointon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Diff against 1.10.6 to fix a couple of the mentioned instances of this problem.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=synchro",
                        "name": "synchro",
                        "displayName": "Marcus Bointon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-07T13:57:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-07T13:57:00.000+0000"
                },
